body:
Problems of a Fellow Fangirl #2

Talking About Infinity War


Cousin: *to my sister* So have you seen Avengers Infin-

Sister: *covers cousin’s mouth* DONT SAY IT!

Cousin: What? Infinity-

Sister: DON’T! We do not speak of it.

Cousin: Why?

Sister: *talks about me* Its because of my sister. If she hears the word Infinity War she-

Me: *breaks room door*

Sister: Oh my god what have I done.

Me: SPIDER-BABY DESERVED BETTER!

Sister: There she goes again.

Me: *angry* I’m as angry as hulk!

Sister: Please calm down-

Me: Calm down! Calm down! HOW ABOUT I STAB YOU AND ASK YOU WHY YOUR BLEEDING HUH!

Sister: *to cousin* Slowly back off-

Me: *rants about Infinity War for hours*

body:
the avengers group chat

  • it’d start with Peter making it, of course
  • he’d be chatting to one of the team some day (probably Bruce?) and ask if there is one
  • ‘what do you mean there’s no group chat?!’
  • cue him making it IMMEDIATELY
  • ‘hi guys welcome 2 the group chat’
  • tony would leave immediately
  • peter would add him back, obviously
  • ‘what’s this for?’ steve would ask
  • ‘so we can keep in touch easily, I guess’ someone else replies (probably natasha tbh)
  • it’ll be like that for a few days
  • not really using it, except for maybe some basic stuff
  • like i feel like the first casual trivial message would come from thor
  • he’d ask a question about where something was or if someone wanted to come do something
  • the next couple weeks, people start to use it more but mostly for avengers stuff
  • peter sends the occasional meme in there - tony thumbs it up and smirks to himself, steve just doesn’t understand at all
  • nat would end up muting it IMMEDIATELY
  • cue steve learning about memes and sending some himself, but they’re all dead memes
  • peter decides to educate thor and steve in how to use memes properly
  • and that’s it, really. they’re doomed
  • because from then on, thor is constantly sending memes
  • 24/7 meme sending
  • with the occasional cute animal picture
  • wanda renames everyone in the chat (with peter’s help- it’s a team effort)
  • steve is ‘grandpa’, tony is ‘iron dad’, nat is ‘sneaky spider’, peter is ‘spider-puppy’, thor is ‘thunder dog’, bruce is ‘tony’s boyfriend’, vision is ‘the real king of asgard’ (much to thor’s annoyance)
  • tony kicks steve out whenever he sends a message in that he ‘cba to deal with’
  • nat has to add him back because everyone else finds it too funny
  • steve does not find it funny at all
  • except for when he does, and he kicks tony out when he’s added back in
  • they’d probably have battles of removing people from the chat
  • but at the end of the day everyone loves it deep down and appreciates peter for making it
  • because they love each other and are a big HAPPY FAMILY

(fuck u infinity war)

summary: Favorite stories from Fantastic Four's and Amazing Spider-Man's first 100 issues, respectively?
question: Favorite stories from Fantastic Four's and Amazing Spider-Man's first 100 issues, respectively?
answer: Realizing now that I’ll never actually flip through all 100 of each for the sake of this one question I’ve had lying in here forever, not with the degree of thought and reflection that would truly require, so winging it: the obvious answers are of course The Final Chapter and the Galactus Saga, but for honorary mentions I’ll say The Amazing Spider-Man #66-67 (The Madness Of Mysterio!/To Squash A Spider!) and Fantastic Four #16-17 (The Micro-World Of Doctor Doom!/Defeated By Doctor Doom!). They both involve multiple baller death traps, the former has Mysterio, and the latter has the truly amazing and criminally underrated Doom line “The fools! They live in peace! They are contented and happy! But I’ll soon put a stop to that!”
